  "target_response": {
    "text": "Creatine timing matters far less than consistency — for your strength goal, taking it daily at whatever time you'll reliably remember is what counts, and the research finds no practical difference between before and after the lift. You don't need a loading phase either: a standard daily amount reaches the same muscle saturation within a few weeks, just more gradually. Take it with a meal if it bothers your stomach, and drink normally through the day. Over the next few weeks of the block, judge it by your training log — steady rep or load progress on the main lifts — rather than the scale, since a little early water-weight gain is normal. One caveat: if you have any kidney condition or take regular medication, clear it with your doctor first.",
